message.content:
We first extract the key figures from the financial statements.

1. Debt to Equity Ratio  
   • Debt is represented by liabilities. In this case the only liability is:  
  – Total Current Liabilities: 1,015,922.54  
   • Owner’s Equity is provided as:  
  – Total Owner's Equity: 29,842,166.21  
   • Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity  
  = 1,015,922.54 / 29,842,166.21  
  ≈ 0.03406  
   Rounding to two decimals, we get 0.03.

2. Net Profit Margin  
   • Net Profit from the income statement is: 1,842,166.21  
   • Total Revenue is: 20,318,450.67  
   • Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (1,842,166.21 / 20,318,450.67) × 100  
  ≈ 9.065%  
   Rounding to two decimals, we get 9.07%.

3. Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
   • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities from the cash flow statement is: -18,924,462.44  
   • Total Current Liabilities is: 1,015,922.54  
   • Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)  
  = -18,924,462.44 / 1,015,922.54  
  ≈ -18.63

Thus, the final results in the required JSON format are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.03",
    "Net Profit Margin": "9.07%",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-18.63"
  }
}
